<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In digital mage manipulation, a special effect which transforms a <a title="Continuous Tone" href="Continuous_Tone">continuous tone</a> image into small dots. Essentially, dots of pure colors are placed adjacent to each other, the viewer perceiving that various intermediate shades are present. (This is somewhat different than <a title="Halftone" href="Halftone">halftone</a> production.) The term derives from (and is meant to simulate) a style of painting popularized by several Impresisonists of the late nineteenth centiuy, (most notably Georges Seurat), also called <em>pointillism</em>. 
</p>
